review_blob: Great white ale, if not the best I have had. Not filling, very refreshing and goes great with a good steak!
Wonderful aroma with hints of chocolate, caramel and some mocha/coffee smells. Nicely smooth beer that is not too carbonated or too heavy
In OK beer for New Belgium, but the after taste is way too tart and bitter for my liking
Great taste, cloudy color and a nice foamy head. A great overall hefe that wont leave you full
Very yellow color beer, with a little head. Not a bad beer but by no means a great beer
CRAPPY CRAPPY CRAPPY!!! The worst of all the available mass produced beers. If you are in a desert dying of thirst, that is the only time I would drink it
I love Shiner being from Texas, but this is a dissapointment for me. A step above the Miller, Bud, Coors stuff but not a great beer at all
In OK Hef, but for the ability to find and the cost, not bad. Good color and aroma though. Left a kind of acid bitter palate
Great color and pretty damn amazing when drunk warm. Another great beer in my opinion from Shiner
Aroma at first I did not like but the taste is GREAT. Gotta love the big 1 Pt. bottle and the not so bad alcohol percentage
Good beer with lots of aromas and a great overall appearance. Not what you would exprect from a "German" style beer but still good
Great taste for being Irish. better than Murphys. Good overall beer but not the best
Good for a fruity beer but not close to the best Sam Adams or any fruit/wheat made but a good warm day beer
Nice aroma of lemon and a refreshing beer. Not what I expected from Sam Adams but overall an OK beer
Great overall beer with a wonderful aroma and color but VERY hard to drink more than 1. Too thick and sweet for me
Not bad for a Canadian beer. Simple and easy to drink beer. Very refreshing but not exactly a "pleasing" beer
Nice full head that slowly evaporates and leaves a perfect medium head everytime you poor and no matter how you poor. Not carbinated at all but a nice, smooth creamy beer.
Great beer that is easy to find. Aroma is a warm banana nut bread smell but taste is a somewhat sweet caramel. Easy to drink many of these

I dont know why it got rated so terribly. Sure it is not an award winning beer but sure as hell beats most mexican beers and is soo easy to drink. When thirsty, Tecate is the next best thing to water for me
A great mexican beer with or without a lime. Blows Corona and many other Mexican beers out of the water. Good for drinking a lot of beer on a warm summer day
I was very disappointed with this beer. Rahr makes some good beers but this is by far the worse. Bad taste, weak aroma and a let down of a beer. Ugly Pug is WAY more exceptional
Good summer beer as it is easy to drink and not get full off of. Not the best beer but better than any bud, miller, coors, etc.
Not very impressed with this beer. Very weak taste, weak head, aroma is the only thing I enjoyed about this beer
Very close to a Miller Light in color and taste but overall a little bit better. Very easy to drink as it is not filling at all
Great beer for being a pretty massed produced beer. Aroma is good, initial taste and aftertaste are fine and the color is wonderful in my opinion
Nice aroma, great color and head, tase a little too bitter finish for me but overall a pretty good beer
Good beer to get drunk off of. Definetely better than BUd Light or Coors Light.
An excellent beer for the money and the availablity is great. I do not understand why most people add an orange when it already has strong hints of orange in the beer.
